    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="340" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <head>No. 340.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Anderson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 27, 1888</date>.
                            (Received March 16.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 210.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that I was informed
                        day before yesterday that the committee of the upper house of the Rigsdag,
                        to which the petroleum bill introduced by the minister of justice has been
                        referred, will doubtless report an amendment to the bill in favor of raising
                        the fire test of petroleum to 40° Celsius, a test equal to that of what is
                        known in America as “water-white” oil.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">R. B.
                            Anderson.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
